(:summary    "Mode for editing programs written in Appel's Tiger language"
 :created    "2001"
 :updated    "2001"
 :license    "GPL"
 :authors    (("Edward O'Connor" . "ted@oconnor.cx"))
 :maintainer ("Edward O'Connor" . "ted@oconnor.cx")
 :provided   (tiger)
 :keywords   (languages)
 :homepage   "http://edward.oconnor.cx/elisp"
 :commentary "\
This mode only supports font-locking, unfortunately. If you'd like
to add functionality, please do so! :) You'll want to add something
like this to your .emacs file:

(require 'tiger)
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '(\"\\\\.tig$\" . tiger-mode))")
